[normal] the extent of the natural variability.
[normal]Furthermore the 
[normal]modelling
[normal] approach is inherently of no value for predicting future temperature with any calculable certainty because of the difficulty of specifying the initial c
[normal]onditions of a large number of variables with sufficient precision prior to multiple iterations. There is no way of knowing whether t
[normal]he outputs after the parameteriz
[normal]ation of the multiple inputs merely hide compensating errors in the system as a whole. 
