[normal]In[bold] summary the projections of the IPCC - Met office models and all the impact studies which derive from them are based on specifically structurally flawed and inherently useless models. They deserve[bold]&#xa0;[bold]no[bold]&#xa0;[bold]place in any serious discussion of future climate trends[bold] and represent an enormous waste of time and money. As a basis for public policy their [bold]forecasts are grossly in error[bold]&#xa0;[bold]and therefore worse than useless.[bold]&#xa0;[bold]The Way Ahead.[bold]A Simple Rational Approach to Climate Forecasting based on Com[bold]mon Sense and Quasi [bold]Repetitive -[bold]&#xa0;[bold]Quasi Cyclic Patterns.[bold]&#xa0;
